items.title: Heisenberg said it was impossible. Scientists just proved otherwise
bullets: • Researchers have reimagined Heisenberg’s uncertainty principle, engineering a trade-off that allows precise measurement of both position and momentum
• Using quantum computing tools like grid states and trapped ions, they demonstrated sensing precision beyond classical limits
• Such advances could revolutionize navigation, medicine, and physics

items.title: Namibia deploys army to fight wildfire burning third of Etosha game reserve
bullets: • Namibia has begun deploying hundreds of soldiers to fight a fire that has burned through a third of Etosha national park
• The park in the north of the largely desert country is home to 114 species of mammals, notably the critically endangered black rhinoceros
• The fire had been burning since 22 September and had caused extensive ecological damage

items.title: The endangered cactus behind Mexico's sweet secret
bullets: • Barches of barrel cactus have been chopped up and seeped in vats of sugar until they're crystalized
• The Mexican government began banning the sale of acitrón in the early 2000s
• The biznaga cactus was found to be in danger of extinction due to overexploitation

items.title: NoViolet Bulawayo wins the Best of Caine award
bullets: • Best of Caine Prize for African Writing is awarded for a short story
• The story examines the lives of a group of children in Budapest, Hungary
• The winner of the award will be announced at the end of the month
• The award was handed out at the British Library in London today

items.title: Tropical Storm Imelda expected to batter parts of the southeastern U.S. this week
bullets: • Parts of the U.S
• are expected to be hit by Tropical Storm I-Bahamas
• The storm is expected to bring heavy rain to parts of the country
• Parts of South Carolina, Florida and Georgia are in the path of the storm
• The hurricane is a tropical depression

items.title: Is taking acetaminophen during pregnancy really associated with autism in children?
bullets: • President Trump suggested that taking acetaminophen during pregnancy is linked to autism in children
• Doctors disagree and say there's no strong evidence for that
• Tylenol could play a role in ongoing legal cases against the company that makes it
• NPR's pharmaceuticals correspondent, Sydney Lupkin, joins us in the comments

items.title: Meteorite collectors gather in Cincinnati this weekend for 'Meet a Meteorite'
bullets: • Meteorite collectors gather in Cincinnati this weekend for 'Meet a Meteorite' The rocks that hurtle from outer space and make it to Earth get a moment to shine
• At the Cincinnati Observatory later today, collectors will be showing off some of their treasures

items.title: Startup founder Charlie Javice reportedly sentenced to 7 years in prison for defrauding JPMorgan Chase

items.title: Etsy pops 15% as OpenAI announces ChatGPT Instant Checkout for the shopping site
bullets: • OpenAI's ChatGPT chatbot Instant Checkout allows users to buy products
• The company will take a fee from transactions that are completed through ChatGpt
• The feature is free to users and will not affect their prices, OpenAI said

items.title: Trump demands Hamas accept US plan to ‘end Gaza conflict’ as Netanyahu says Israel will ‘finish the job’ if they don’t – live
bullets: • Hamas official says group has not received written Trump's Gaza peace plan

• He gave the remarks in an interview with Al Jazeera Mubasher TV shortly after Trump’s joint press conference with Benjamin Netanyahu in which the Israeli prime minister expressed support for the plan

items.title: Portland braces for deployment of 200 national guard troops to city
bullets: • Portland is bracing for the deployment of 200 national guard troops
• Oregon filed a lawsuit to block the deployment, which the state has warned will escalate tensions
• The president has frequently sought to paint the city as out of control and, as he described in September, like ‘living in hell”

items.title: Body of missing teen found in D4vd’s Tesla likely ‘dead for several weeks,’ says police
bullets: • Celeste Rivas Hernandez was found dead in the trunk of D4vd’s Tesla in early September
• Los Angeles police say it is likely she had been dead for several weeks prior to her body being discovered
• The then 13-year-old was first reported missing on 5 April 2024

items.title: Afghanistan telecom blackout as Taliban shuts off internet
bullets: • Afghanistan telecom blackout as Taliban shuts off internet services across the country
• The Taliban have imposed a total blackout of internet services in accordance with their Islamic law
• Many people will not notice the impact until Tuesday morning, when services are expected to resume
• The country is experiencing a total connectivity blackout

items.title: F-Droid says Google’s new sideloading restrictions will kill the project
bullets: • F-Droid is the largest app store for Android software
• Google recently announced plans to force app developers to verify their apps
• Apps that have not been validated by the company will not be installed on any Android device
• F-Froid says the move will not stop apps from being installed in the Play Store

items.title: Watch: Trump details plan to end Israel war with Hamas in Gaza
bullets: • The White House released a 20-point plan to end the war in Gaza between Israel and Hamas
• The plan calls for Gaza to be governed under the temporary transitional governance of a technocratic, apolitical Palestinian committee
• If Hamas rejects the plan, "they're the only one left," President Trump says

items.title: Florida man killed, cooked and ate two of his pet peacocks, say authorities
bullets: • Craig Vogt, 61, was arrested on 23 September on a third-degree felony charge of aggravated animal cruelty
• He allegedly told investigators that he had killed the two peacocks because his neighbor kept feeding them
• He had written the neighbor a letter telling her that he would continue to kill his pet peacocks if she continued feeding them “to prove a point”

items.title: Madagascar’s president dissolves government amid youth-led protests
bullets: • President Andry Rajoelina has dissolved the government after youth-led protests over water and power cuts

• Thousands of people have marched in the capital Antananarivo since demonstrations began last week

items.title: Democrats refuse to cave on health care before meeting with Trump on government shutdown
bullets: • House Democratic Leader Hakeem Jeffries: "Enough with the games that Republicans have been playing connected to the health care of the American people" Republicans insist that any deal must extend enhanced Obamacare tax credits that are due to expire at the end of 2025

items.title: Nine people dead and scores injured over weekend of mass US shootings
bullets: • Six mass shootings erupted across the US over the weekend, killing nine people and injuring at least 33
• The Gun Violence Archive, an online non-profit database which records mass shootings in America, added six fresh incidents over Saturday and Sunday
• The archive’s tally of mass shootings – defined as events with at least four victims injured or killed, not counting the shooter – is 324 this year alone

items.title: Labor Dept. won't release Friday's key jobs report, other data if government shuts down
bullets: • The Labor Department is preparing for what would amount to a news and data blackout
• The DOL, in conjunction with the Bureau of Labor Statistics, has several key reports upcoming that will provide important clues about the direction of the economy

items.title: Investigators search for motive in deadly Michigan church attack
bullets: • Four people killed and eight injured in Michigan church attack on Sunday
• Thomas Jacob Sanford, 40, drove his vehicle into a church, opened fire and then set it ablaze
• Hundreds of people were attending a service at the time, and police said on Monday that everyone had been accounted for
• Governor Gretchen Whitmer called for patience as FBI works to determine a motive

items.title: ESA will pay an Italian company nearly $50 million to design a mini-Starship
bullets: • The European Space Agency signs a deal with Avio to design a reusable upper stage

items.title: Wildfire in Namibia is contained, says PM, after criticism of response
bullets: • The fire broke out in Etosha national park, in Namibia's north, on 22 September

items.title: Senators try to halt shuttle move, saying “little evidence” of public demand

items.title: West Africans deported from US to Ghana ‘dumped without documents in Togo’

items.title: Fortnite disables Peacemaker emote that might resemble a swastika

items.title: Taiwan pressured to move 50% of chip production to US or lose protection

items.title: Trump considering supplying Ukraine with long-range missiles, Vance says

items.title: Lesotho's Famo music: from shepherd songs to gang wars
bullets: • Lesotho's Famo music is a popular genre of pastoral accordion music beloved by the country's people
• Puseletso Seema is known as "the Queen of Famo" but her living conditions are far from regal
• Famo is a music that is emotionally connected, you can express your happiness, sadness, all your feelings

items.title: YouTuber MrBeast defends trapping man in burning building for $500,000

items.title: Lawsuits against Tylenol's maker get a boost after Trump's comments

items.title: Sen. Amy Klobuchar talks about the potential for a government shutdown

items.title: Moldova's pro-EU party wins clear parliamentary majority, defeating pro-Russian groups

items.title: Scared of spiders? Some former arachnophobes now are keeping jumping spiders as pets

items.title: Hubble finds a hybrid galaxy with a mysterious and violent past

items.title: Earth was born dry until a cosmic collision made it a blue planet
bullets: • Earth was born dry until a cosmic collision made it a blue planet
• Initially, the planet was barren and inhospitable, missing water and carbon compounds
• A colossal collision with Theia likely changed everything, bringing the essential ingredients for life
• Study highlights that habitability may hinge on rare chance events

items.title: Black hole discovery confirms Einstein and Hawking were right
bullets: • New observations of a merger of two black holes confirm decades-old predictions by Albert Einstein, Stephen Hawking and Roy Kerr
• Scientists tracked the complete cosmic collision, confirming that black holes are defined by mass and spin
• They also gained stronger proof that a black hole’s event horizon only grows, echoing thermodynamic laws

items.title: Fossils in germany reveal a Jurassic sea monster with a swordfish snout

items.title: Amazon’s Echo Pop and Dot speakers are the cheapest they’ve been in months

items.title: The best instant cameras you can buy right now
